'''Austin Williams''' (born November 13, 1996) is an [[United States|American]] [[soap opera]] [[actor]]. In 2005, Austin was cast in the film ''[[The Good Shepherd (film)|The Good Shepherd]]'', which starred Matt Damon, as the young version of Damon's character Edward Wilson. In October 2007, he was cast in the role of [[Shane Morasco]] on ''[[One Life to Live]]'', a role that continues today In 2008, he was nominated for a Young Artist Award for "Best Performance in a Feature Film - Young Actor Age Ten or Younger" for his role as Henry Clayton in the 2007 film ''[[Michael Clayton (film)|Michael Clayton]]''. Austin currently attends Bergen County Academies which is an elite high school in Hackensack, New Jersey.
Williams has a younger sister [[Amber Joy Williams]] who is an actress. Both appeared in ''[[Home Movie (2008 film)|Home Movie]]'' as twins.
